The FREELAND PROCESS COMPANY v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE. No. 2101. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. April 12, 1940. J. E. Hart, of Tulsa, Okl., for petitioner. J. P. Wenchel, Chief Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before PHILLIPS, BRATTON, and WILLIAMS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petition dismissed on motion of petitioner.
